<paragraph id="8BCB9B10FFA3FF87FF7FFBD8FB662386" blockId="3.[192,1441,1047,1492]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C74E093FFA3FF87FF7FFBD8FEAC227D" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" box="[232,350,1047,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FF7FFBD8FEAC227D" box="[232,350,1047,1071]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE5E6E1FFA3FF87FDA0FBD7FCF02262" author="Chevrolat, L. A." box="[567,770,1048,1072]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="451 - 504" refId="ref11462" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1860. Description d'especes de Clytus propres au Mexique. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (3) 8: 451 - 504." type="journal article" year="1860">Chevrolat (1860)</bibRefCitation>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C74E093FFA3FF87FC43FBD8FAF72262" authority="Laicharting, 1784" authorityName="Laicharting" authorityYear="1784" box="[980,1285,1047,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Clytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FC43FBD8FBD1227D" box="[980,1059,1047,1071]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Clytus</emphasis>
Laicharting, 1784
</taxonomicName>
. He included 14 species in the group but did not designate a 
<typeStatus id="54CF25B2FFA3FF87FD69FBF6FCC12203" box="[766,819,1081,1105]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
species. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE5E6E1FFA3FF87FC66FBF7FB472202" author="Thomson, J." box="[1009,1205,1080,1104]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref12693" refString="Thomson, J. 1861. Tribu. Cerambycitae. p. 129 - 396. In: J. Thomson. Essai d'une classification de la famille des cerambycides et materiaux pour servir a une monographie de cette famille. Chez l'auteur et au Bureau du Tresorier de la Societe entomologique de France; Paris. 396 p." type="book" year="1861">Thomson (1861)</bibRefCitation>
elevated 
<taxonomicName id="4C74E093FFA3FF87FABDFBF7FA522202" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" box="[1322,1440,1080,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FABDFBF7FA522202" box="[1322,1440,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to genus level and designated 
<taxonomicName id="4C74E093FFA3FF87FDA4FB97FBAF2222" authority="Chevrolat, 1860" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" box="[563,1117,1112,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Clytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilineatus" subGenus="Trichoxys">
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FDA4FB97FD702222" box="[563,642,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Clytus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FD05FB97FCFA2222" box="[658,776,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FC8EFB97FC612222" box="[793,915,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">bilineatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE5E6E1FFA3FF87FC0DFB96FBAF2222" author="Chevrolat, L. A." box="[922,1117,1112,1137]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="451 - 504" refId="ref11462" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1860. Description d'especes de Clytus propres au Mexique. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (3) 8: 451 - 504." type="journal article" year="1860">Chevrolat, 1860</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus id="54CF25B2FFA3FF87FB1FFB96FB4F2223" box="[1160,1213,1113,1137]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C74E093FFA3FF87FABDFB97FA522222" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" box="[1322,1440,1112,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FABDFB97FA522222" box="[1322,1440,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently composed of 15 species, all of them recorded for 
<collectingCountry id="F363DB80FFA3FF87FC3FFBB6FC0C22C3" box="[936,1022,1145,1169]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Mexico</collectingCountry>
with five of the species extending their known distribution into Central America (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE5E6E1FFA3FF87FD61FB56FB8822E3" author="Tavakilian, G. &amp; H. Chevillotte" box="[758,1146,1177,1201]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref12647" refString="Tavakilian, G., and H. Chevillotte. 2018. Titan, base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou longicornes. Version 3.0. Available at http: // titan. gbif. fr /. (Last accessed 2018 December.)" type="url" year="2018">Tavakilian and Chevillotte 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE5E6E1FFA3FF87FB13FB56FAEC22E3" author="Bezark, L. G." box="[1156,1310,1177,1201]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref11231" refString="Bezark, L. G. 2019. A Photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the New World. Available at https: // apps 2. cdfa. ca. gov / publicApps / plant / bycidDB / wsearch. asp? w = n (Last accessed January 2019.)" type="url" year="2019">Bezark 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE5E6E1FFA3FF87FF57FB75FDCC2280" author="Lingafelter, S. W. &amp; J. E. Wappes" box="[192,574,1210,1234]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="154 - 162" refId="ref11848" refString="Lingafelter, S. W., and J. E. Wappes. 2012. A new species of Trichoxys Chevrolat (Cerambycidae: Cerambycinae: Clytini) from Mexico, with a key to known species. The Pan-Pacific Entomologist 88 (2): 154 - 162." type="journal article" year="2012">Lingafelter and Wappes (2012)</bibRefCitation>
provided a diagnosis for the genus as follows: “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C74E093FFA3FF87FB1CFB76FA712280" authority="Chevrolat" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" box="[1163,1411,1209,1234]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FB1CFB76FAF32283" box="[1163,1281,1209,1233]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys</emphasis>
Chevrolat
</taxonomicName>
is characterized from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C74E093FFA3FF87FE67FB15FDB722A0" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1839" box="[496,581,1242,1266]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Clytini">Clytini</taxonomicName>
by 1) the abruptly recessed parasutural region of the elytron that starts at the anterior one-third and diverges more widely to the apex where it is approximately one-third of the discal width, and the strongly elevated anterior portion of the mesosternum (appearing abruptly recessed from ventral view) and 2) the evenly rounded pronotum that is distinctly narrower than the elytral base and without calli or lateral asymmetry. All the known species have bold, pubescent patterns on the elytra which are easily diagnostic for each species.” They also placed 
<taxonomicName id="4C74E093FFA3FF87FBF9FAB4FE9723E6" authority="Linsley, 1935" authorityName="Linsley" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochraetheoides">
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FBF9FAB4FA5223C1" box="[1134,1440,1403,1427]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys ochraetheoides</emphasis>
Linsley, 
<quantity id="4C8C36F5FFA3FF87FEBDFA53FE9723E6" box="[298,357,1436,1460]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.914899999999999" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="1935.0">1935</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="4C74E093FFA3FF87FDC7FA52FC4B23E6" authority="(Chevrolat, 1860)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[592,953,1436,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FDC7FA52FD2B23E6" box="[592,729,1436,1460]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">T. hirtellus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE5E6E1FFA3FF87FD7EFA53FC4223E6" author="Chevrolat, L. A." box="[745,944,1436,1460]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="451 - 504" refId="ref11462" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1860. Description d'especes de Clytus propres au Mexique. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (3) 8: 451 - 504." type="journal article" year="1860">Chevrolat, 1860</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, described 
<taxonomicName id="4C74E093FFA3FF87FBD6FA52FB3523E1" authorityName="Lingafelter &amp; Wappes" authorityYear="2012" box="[1089,1223,1436,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penrosei">
<emphasis id="B9004702FFA3FF87FBD6FA52FB3523E1" box="[1089,1223,1436,1460]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">T. penrosei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new species, and provided a key to the species based on their illustrations of elytral patterns.
</paragraph>
